result.execSummary:
David B Vasey was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means David B Vasey was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Attorney Stephen Andrew Sargent in court.  Annie Louk appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Attorney appeared by video means for .  Defendant has been turned over to the State of MINNESOTA on April 14, 2022
On motion of the state, Court ordered case closed.

Defendant David B Vasey in court with attorney Vincent Paul Guimont.  Defendant David B Vasey in custody.  Jennifer Jean Tate appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  David B Vasey appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45.  Court reviewed complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of rights and right to file a Writ of Habeas Corpus.  Court found the defendant is the person wanted in the State of Minnesota.  Defendant waived extradition.  Signed Waiver of Extradition received and filed.  Court ordered the defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Status conference scheduled for May 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
